# PuzzleMetrics — Cursor Rules

## Project
- Company: PuzzleMetrics — UK-based AI services company
- Stack: Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, Framer Motion, Three.js, Prisma, PostgreSQL
- All components use the `'use client'` directive only when needed (hooks, events, animations)
- Server components by default, client components only when required

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, always type everything
- Use named exports for components, default exports for pages
- File naming: PascalCase for components, kebab-case for pages/routes
- Always use `@/` import alias, never relative imports like `../../`
- Prefer `const` arrow functions for components: `const MyComponent = () => {}`
- No inline styles — use Tailwind classes only
- Group imports: React → Next.js → third-party → internal → types

## Design System — NEVER deviate from these tokens
- Brand violet: #6055D9
- Violet dark: #3D34B0
- Violet light: #EDEAFF
- Background (light): #FAFAFE
- Stone (alt bg): #F4F3FC
- Ink (text): #0D0B1A
- Mid (secondary text): #4A4870
- Muted: #8A87B0
- Border: #D6D3F0
- Dark bg: #08071A
- Dark surface: #0F0E28

## Fonts (loaded via next/font in layout.tsx)
- Headings: Syne 800 — var(--font-syne)
- Body: DM Sans 300/400/500 — var(--font-sans)
- Mono: DM Mono 400 — var(--font-mono)
- Accent quotes: Playfair Display 700 italic — var(--font-playfair)

## Tailwind Config
- darkMode: 'class' — dark mode via class on <html>
- All brand colours extended in tailwind.config.ts
- Custom tokens: rounded-card (16px), rounded-btn (12px)

## Animations
- Use Framer Motion for ALL scroll and entry animations
- Define reusable variants in src/lib/animations.ts
- Always use `whileInView` with `viewport={{ once: true, amount: 0.2 }}`
- Always add SSR guard: `if (typeof window === 'undefined') return`
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion in all animation variants
- Three.js globe: lazy load with `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })`
- Never render Three.js on mobile — use static SVG fallback below 768px

## Dark Mode Rules
- Toggle adds/removes 'dark' class on `document.documentElement` — NEVER on body
- Read from localStorage key `'pm-theme'` on mount, apply before first paint
- Partner/client logos in dark mode: use explicit white SVG fills — NEVER CSS `filter: invert()`

## Auth & Security
- JWT stored in httpOnly + secure + sameSite:'lax' cookies — NEVER localStorage
- Every /admin API route must verify JWT and check role before any operation
- super_admin: full access | chat_operator: /admin/chat only
- Rate limit: /api/auth/login (5/min), /api/contact (10/min), /api/newsletter (20/min)

## Database
- Prisma ORM with PostgreSQL
- Prisma client singleton in src/lib/db.ts
- Always use transactions for multi-table writes
- Never expose raw Prisma errors to the client

## File Structure
- src/app/                        → Next.js App Router pages
- src/app/admin/                  → Admin panel routes (all protected)
- src/app/api/                    → API route handlers
- src/components/public/layout/   → Navbar, Footer, LoaderScreen
- src/components/public/home/     → Hero, TickerStrip, Services, Process, Platforms, Partners, SocialProof, CTABand, Newsletter
- src/components/public/shared/   → Button, Card, Badge, Input, SectionLabel
- src/components/admin/           → All admin UI components
- src/components/chat/            → ChatWidget (public), ChatPanel (admin)
- src/lib/                        → db.ts, auth.ts, email.ts, upload.ts, animations.ts
- src/hooks/                      → useCountUp, useScrollAnimation, useTheme, useChatSocket
- src/types/                      → All TypeScript interfaces
- src/middleware.ts                → JWT protection for all /admin/* routes
- public/                         → logo.svg, favicon.ico, og-image.jpg

